{"word":"G4805 - σύζυγος - sýzygos - sood'-zoo-gos - Yokefellow","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">σύζυγος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">sýzygos</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">sood'-zoo-gos</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Yokefellow</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Adjective / பெயரடை</span>"},{"paragraph":"கூட்டாளியான - பெயரடை"},{"paragraph":"yoked together"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>From <a href=\"#/G4801 - συζεύγνυμι - syzeúgnymi - sood-zyoog'-noo-mee/4801\">G4801</a>; <i>co-yoked</i>, that is, (figuratively) as noun, a <i>colleague</i>; probably rather as proper name; <i>Syzygus</i>, a Christian: - yokefellow.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}